[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue Definition  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The issue is a runtime error reported by libFuzzer stating that the fuzzer has [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhit its timeout limit and aborted the testing session. No further information about[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcrashes, hangs, or specific inputs is provided—only that the overall fuzzing run [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdid not finish within the expected time.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability Type  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The issue description does not specify a particular security vulnerability [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g.,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer overflow, use-after-free[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. Instead, it points to a performance or [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtermination problem in the target code under fuzz testing.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Observations and Findings  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The fuzzer harness itself is only the entry point for fuzzing and is not [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnecessarily the root cause of the timeout.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • A timeout generally arises when the code under test enters a long-running loop,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeadlock, unbounded recursion, or expensive computation that exceeds libFuzzer’s [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtime budget.  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • No crash or sanitizer report accompanied the timeout, suggesting that the code [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmay be hanging or taking excessively long on certain inputs rather than triggering [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma low-level fault.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The absence of input-specific logs implies that the issue may manifest broadly [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39macross multiple fuzzing inputs or under specific edge-case conditions that [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrepeatedly exhaust time limits.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Code Areas for Investigation  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  To obtain a holistic view of why the fuzzer timed out, examine:  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The harness entry point – verify how inputs are fed into the library or API [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munder test.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Loops and recursion – identify any unbounded or poorly constrained loops that [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcould stall processing.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Heavy computations – locate cryptographic routines, data-structure operations, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor algorithms with worst-case performance issues.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Synchronization constructs – check for potential deadlocks, mutex waits, or [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mblocking I/O calls that do not return promptly.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Error-handling and retry logic – look for infinite retry loops or blocking [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merror states when encountering unexpected input.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBy systematically reviewing these components, you can map out where the code may [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfail to terminate in a reasonable time and thereby trigger the libFuzzer timeout.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mERROR: libFuzzer: timeout[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95missue[0m[39m>[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Analysis [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Analysis Report[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Relevant Code Snippets[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_snippets>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m387[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Overview  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The libFuzzer timeout indicates the PDF parser is stuck in long-running loops [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munder malformed or fuzzed inputs. The critical areas are:  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Backward EOF/startxref scan in [0m[1;35mCOSParser.getStartxrefOffset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Cross-reference chain loop in [0m[1;35mXrefParser.parseXref[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Potentially unbounded parsing in [0m[1;35mparseXrefTable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m[1;35mparseXrefObjStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39minside XrefParser[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Strategy Summary  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Bound the trailing-bytes scan to prevent overly large buffers.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Validate the computed startxref offset against file length and fail fast on [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvalid offsets.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Introduce iteration limits in the XRef chain loop to break out on too many [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msegments.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   D. [0m[1;39m([0m[39mOptional but recommended[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Add entry-count limits in parseXrefTable and [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparseXrefObjStream to avoid millions of entries.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Step-by-step Fix  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Clamp EOF lookup range  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – In COSParser constructor [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor static init[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, replace system-property [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverride:  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        • Read `SYSPROP_EOFLOOKUPRANGE` as before, but then:  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnewRange > MAX_EOF_LOOKUP[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m log warning and use MAX_EOF_LOOKUP [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minstead.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        • Define `MAX_EOF_LOOKUP` as a safe upper bound [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. 64k[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Validate startxref offset  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – After computing `long result = skipBytes + bufOff;` in [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mgetStartxrefOffset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mresult < [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m || result > fileLen[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           if [0m[1;39m([0m[39misLenient[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m log debug and return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfall back to brute-force[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           else throw [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Invalid startxref offset: "[0m[39m + result[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Limit XRef chain iterations  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – In [0m[1;35mXrefParser.parseXref[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: before the `while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mprev > [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m && prev != [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlastPrev[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` loop, add:  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         int xrefLoopCount = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – At top of loop, increment and check:  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m++xrefLoopCount > MAX_XREF_CHAIN[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Too many XRef chain iterations: "[0m[39m + [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxrefLoopCount[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        Choose `MAX_XREF_CHAIN` small [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. [0m[1;36m50[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   D. [0m[1;39m([0m[39mOptional[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Bound entries in parseXrefTable/parseXrefObjStream  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – In both methods, maintain a counter of processed entries; if it exceeds [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMAX_XREF_ENTRIES [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. 1_000_000[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, abort with IOException.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Preservation of existing behavior  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Valid PDFs have a limited number of XRef segments and entries; our limits [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39me.g. [0m[1;36m50[0m[39m segments, 1M entries[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are orders of magnitude above normal usage.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Lenient mode still allows fallback brute-force parse, only with validated [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moffsets.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – EOF lookup remains default [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2048[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m unless expressly increased within safe[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mceiling.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Justification  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Prevents degenerate or fuzzed inputs from driving parser loops into excessive [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwork, thus avoiding fuzzer timeouts.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Fails fast on invalid or malicious markers, preserving resource bounds.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Limits are configurable constants near default behavior and unlikely to affect[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalid documents.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Potential Side Effects & Mitigations  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Extremely large but valid PDFs with many incremental updates could exceed XRef[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchain limit; mitigate by raising MAX_XREF_CHAIN if real-world documents need it.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Very large trailing garbage plus HTML could require more EOF lookup bytes; [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclamp safely [0m[1;39m([0m[39m64k[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m but allow override up to that.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Write unit tests to ensure common real-world PDFs still parse.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. References  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Similar loop-count safeguard in COSParser.getStartxrefOffset’s read loop [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malready checks readBytes < [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m to avoid infinite.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Add symmetric safeguards in XrefParser chain loop and entry parsing.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue reported a libFuzzer timeout when parsing PDF files. To address [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpotential infinite loops and unbounded searches, the patch attempt introduced two [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmain changes:  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. In COSParser:[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A new constant `MAX_EOF_LOOKUP` and logic in `setEOFLookupRange` to cap the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlookup range.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Additional handling in `getStartxrefOffset` to search for the last “%%EOF” [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmarker, apply lenient fallbacks, and validate the computed startxref offset.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. In XrefParser:[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A new constant `MAX_XREF_CHAIN` and a counter in the xref-chain parsing loop [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto prevent excessive iterations.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the build failed with a compilation error in COSParser: [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe variable `bufOff` is declared twice in the method `[0m[1;35mgetStartxrefOffset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcausing a duplicate-definition error.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer reported a “timeout” in the PDF parsing code, indicating that certain [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minputs may cause the parser to loop indefinitely or process excessively large [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msections of the file without termination.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No stack trace or location was provided beyond the timeout mechanism of [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibFuzzer.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `COSParser.java` around line [0m[1;36m224[0m[39m:[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Added `public static final int MAX_EOF_LOOKUP = [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m * [0m[1;36m1024[0m[39m;`  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Updated `[0m[1;35msetEOFLookupRange[0m[1;39m([0m[39mint byteCount[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to enforce the maximum and log a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwarning if exceeded.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `[0m[1;35mCOSParser.getStartxrefOffset[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` around lines [0m[1;36m347[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m379[0m[39m:[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Inserted logic to locate the last occurrence of the EOF marker in the buffer.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Handled missing markers in lenient mode and error mode.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Changed the return path to validate that the computed offset is within `[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfileLen[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, with lenient fallback or IOException.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `XrefParser.java` around line [0m[1;36m44[0m[39m and loop at [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m:[0m                              [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Introduced `xrefLoopCount` to throw an IOException after too many iterations.[0m   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Reapply and correct the EOF‐lookup cap in COSParser.setEOFLookupRange:[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Retain the new constant [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      `public static final int MAX_EOF_LOOKUP = [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m * [0m[1;36m1024[0m[39m;`[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      alongside other class constants.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. In `[0m[1;35msetEOFLookupRange[0m[1;39m([0m[39mint byteCount[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, compute a bounded value:[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      int newCount = [0m[1;35mMath.min[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyteCount, MAX_EOF_LOOKUP[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyteCount > MAX_EOF_LOOKUP[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mLOG.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"System property [0m[32m{[0m[32m}[0m[32m is too large: [0m[32m{[0m[32m}[0m[32m, using max [0m[32m{[0m[32m}[0m[32m"[0m[39m,[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                   SYSPROP_EOFLOOKUPRANGE, byteCount, MAX_EOF_LOOKUP[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnewCount > [0m[1;36m15[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          readTrailBytes = newCount;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. This preserves the original threshold [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m15[0m[39m bytes minimum[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m while enforcing the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mupper bound and logging.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Fix the duplicate‐declaration error in [0m[1;35mCOSParser.getStartxrefOffset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Locate the method signature:[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      private long [0m[1;35mgetStartxrefOffset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Remove any second `int bufOff = [0m[33m...[0m[39m` in the inserted block. Keep only one [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeclaration at the first occurrence:[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m find last [0m[32m'%%EOF'[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      int bufOff = [0m[1;35mlastIndexOf[0m[1;39m([0m[39mEOF_MARKER, buf, buf.length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Replace any subsequent redeclarations with simple assignments:[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m locate [0m[32m'startxref'[0m[39m before the EOF marker[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      bufOff = [0m[1;35mlastIndexOf[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSTARTXREF, buf, bufOff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbufOff < [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Missing 'startxref' marker."[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          long result = skipBytes + bufOff;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mresult < [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m || result > fileLen[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35misLenient[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                  [0m[1;35mLOG.debug[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Invalid startxref offset: [0m[32m{[0m[32m}[0m[32m"[0m[39m, result[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                  return 0L; [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m lenient fallback[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                  throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Invalid startxref offset: "[0m[39m + result[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return result;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. This change eliminates the duplicate `bufOff` definition, fixing the [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompilation error, and preserves both the EOF‐search and new offset‐validation [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogic.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Enforce a maximum XRef‐chain depth in XrefParser without altering existing loop [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msemantics:[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Add the new constant near the top of `XrefParser.java` alongside `XREF_TABLE`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand `STARTXREF`:[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[39m** Maximum allowed iterations for XRef chain parsing to avoid infinite [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloops. *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      private static final int MAX_XREF_CHAIN = [0m[1;36m50[0m[39m;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Immediately before the PREV‐chain loop, declare a counter:[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      int xrefLoopCount = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. At the start of the loop body, increment and check:[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mprev > [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m && prev != lastPrev[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m++xrefLoopCount > MAX_XREF_CHAIN[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Too many XRef chain iterations: "[0m[39m + [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxrefLoopCount[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          lastPrev = prev;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m existing parsing code …[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. This meets the requirement to bound the PREV‐chain length without disturbing [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe existing parsing flow or tests.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Validate and preserve existing functionality:[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The original behavior for files shorter than `readTrailBytes`, lenient mode, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand strict mode is unaltered.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The new upper bounds guard against unbounded loops/timeouts, addressing the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzer‐reported hang.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No harness code, tests, or external libraries are modified.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Potential side effects and mitigations:[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Extremely large `SYSPROP_EOFLOOKUPRANGE` values will now log a warning; ensure[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogging does not degrade performance in high‐throughput scenarios.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The `MAX_XREF_CHAIN` limit should be configurable if PDFs legitimately chain [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmore than [0m[1;36m50[0m[39m cross‐references; adjust only if necessary under controlled testing.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis strategy removes the duplicate‐definition error, reintroduces the intended [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minfinite‐loop safeguards, and maintains backward compatibility with existing PDF [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing logic. [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Too many tokens in stream parsing: "[0m[39m + [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtokenCount[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return streamObjects;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--- a/pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/BruteForceParser.java[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+++ b/pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/BruteForceParser.java[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m@@ [0m[1;36m-140[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m +[0m[1;36m140[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m14[0m[39m @@[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         char[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m endobjString = [0m[32m"ndo"[0m[1;35m.toCharArray[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         char[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m endobjRemainingString = [0m[32m"bj"[0m[1;35m.toCharArray[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         boolean endOfObjFound = false;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        int bruteForceLoopCount = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        final int MAX_BRUTE_FORCE_ITERATIONS = [0m[1;36m100000[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         do[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m++bruteForceLoopCount > MAX_BRUTE_FORCE_ITERATIONS[0m[1;39m)[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Too many iterations in brute force parser: [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"[0m[39m + bruteForceLoopCount[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35msource.seek[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcurrentOffset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             int nextChar = [0m[1;35msource.read[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             currentOffset++;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Patch [0m[33mResult[0m[39m===[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mERROR: libFuzzer: timeout[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===[0m[33mIssue[0m[39m===[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mERROR: libFuzzer: timeout[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe project’s libFuzzer harness reports a timeout when exercising PDFBox parsing [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mroutines. An initial patch was applied to COSParser and XrefParser to  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Cap EOF‐lookup range to [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m KB,  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Validate and bound the computed startxref offset, and  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Limit XRef chain traversal to [0m[1;36m50[0m[39m iterations.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying these changes, the fuzzer still hits a timeout [0m[1;39m([0m[39mno crash, just [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhanging or excessive runtime[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - libFuzzer runs against the PDFBox codebase and reports  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     `ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout`  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No stack trace or exception is produced; the harness simply exceeds the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallotted execution time on certain inputs.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This indicates a likely infinite loop, extremely large loop bound, or very [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexpensive work path in the parser when handling malformed or adversarial PDFs.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key Observations  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The harness exercises PDF parsing routines beginning in `COSParser` and [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`XrefParser`.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The timeout suggests inefficient or unbounded loops rather than outright [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcrashes or uncaught exceptions.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No other errors or log messages appear in the fuzzer output beyond the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtimeout.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. In `COSParser.java`  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Introduced `MAX_EOF_LOOKUP = [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m * [0m[1;36m1024[0m[39m`.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - In `[0m[1;35msetEOFLookupRange[0m[1;39m([0m[39mint byteCount[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, if the requested range exceeds [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MAX_EOF_LOOKUP`, log a warning and clamp to the maximum.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - In `[0m[1;35mparseStartXref[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m353[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, computed `result = skipBytes + [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbufOff` is now checked:  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        • If `result < [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m` or `result > fileLen`, then in lenient mode return 0L [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith a debug log; otherwise throw `IOException`.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. In `XrefParser.java`  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Added `MAX_XREF_CHAIN = [0m[1;36m50[0m[39m`.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - In the loop parsing chained XRef tables, increment `xrefLoopCount` each [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39miteration and throw `IOException` if the count exceeds the maximum.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   After recompiling with these changes, the fuzzer still times out without [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproducing a crash or error message other than the timeout itself.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   To obtain a more complete picture of why the fuzzer hangs, the following code [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregions and behaviors should be audited:  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Other unbounded loops in PDF parsing [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., object-stream parsing, [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtokenization loops, whitespace skipping methods[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The buffer-filling and look-ahead logic in `COSParser.fillBuffer` [0m[35m/[0m[39m `readByte`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[39m `peekByte`, which may loop indefinitely on malformed input.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Trailer parsing and incremental-update handling in `TrailerParser` or similar [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclasses, which may traverse multiple linked structures.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Stream decoding loops [0m[1;39m([0m[39mFlate, LZW, ASCII-[0m[1;36m85[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, especially if successive [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfailures can trigger repeated retries or re-reads.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The harness entry point itself: ensure that timeouts are not caused by waiting[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mon I/O or synchronization rather than parser logic.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mERROR: libFuzzer: timeout[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95missue[0m[39m>[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Additional Issue Log[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the additional issue log after the last patch attempt:[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<additional_issue>[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mERROR: libFuzzer: timeout[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95madditional_issue[0m[39m>[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Notes[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All patch attempts are applied to the initial codebase. Reapply the the previous [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatches if needed.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- If multiple different issues are present, all the issues must be resolved in a [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msingle patch attempt.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Try different approaches to resolve the issues.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Analysis [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Analysis Report[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         +                [35m/[0m[35m/[0m No progress possible: abort to prevent infinite loop            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         +                bytesDecoded = [1;36m0[0m;                                                  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                  catch [1m([0mDataFormatException exception[1m)[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                  [1m{[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         @@ [1;36m-112[0m,[1;36m7[0m +[1;36m120[0m,[1;36m7[0m @@                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                              [1;35mexception.getMessage[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m[1m)[0m;                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                      return bytesDecoded > [1;36m0[0m;                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                  [1m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m              [1m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              [35m/[0m**                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Patch [33mResult[0m===                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===[33mIssue[0m===                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The initial issue reports a libFuzzer timeout when exercising PDFBox’s parsing      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         code. In response, the patch attempt adds upper bounds and iteration limits in      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         several parser classes [1m([0mCOSParser, XrefParser, PDFStreamParser, BruteForceParser[1m)[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         to detect and abort long-running loops or invalid offsets. After applying these     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         changes, the fuzzer still reports the same timeout, indicating the problem          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         persists.                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. Initial Issue                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Fuzzer log: “ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout”                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - No additional stack trace or exception; the harness simply stalled until the   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         fuzzer’s timeout threshold was reached.                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. Observations from the Initial Issue                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The timeout suggests a long-running or potentially infinite loop in PDF        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         parsing code.                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - No explicit exceptions or errors in the logs—execution hung rather than        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         crashing.                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The fuzzer entry point [1m([0mharness[1m)[0m is unaffected; it merely calls into the PDF   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         parser layers.                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. Patch Attempt Details                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            The patch introduces conservative limits and checks in four parser classes:      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            a. COSParser.java                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m               - Added a constant `MAX_EOF_LOOKUP = [1;36m64[0m * [1;36m1024[0m`.                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m               - Modified `[1;35msetEOFLookupRange[0m[1m([0mint byteCount[1m)[0m` to cap `byteCount` at           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `MAX_EOF_LOOKUP`, logging a warning if exceeded.                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m               - In `[1;35mgetStartXrefOffset[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`, changed the raw return of `skipBytes + bufOff`   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         to a guarded `long result`; if `result` is negative or beyond `fileLen`, the code   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         now either logs a debug message and returns `0L` [1m([0mlenient mode[1m)[0m or throws an        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         IOException.                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            b. XrefParser.java                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m               - Introduced `MAX_XREF_CHAIN = [1;36m50[0m`.                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m               - In the loop that follows the `Prev` chain, a new counter `xrefLoopCount` is [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         incremented each iteration; if it exceeds the maximum, an IOException is thrown to  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         prevent infinite chaining.                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            c. PDFStreamParser.java                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m               - Introduced `MAX_STREAM_PARSE_TOKENS = [1;36m10000[0m`.                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m               - In the token-parsing loop, a `tokenCount` is incremented; exceeding the     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         limit triggers an IOException to break out of an endless token stream.              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            d. BruteForceParser.java                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m               - Added `MAX_BRUTE_FORCE_ITERATIONS = [1;36m100000[0m` and a counter                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `bruteForceLoopCount`.                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m               - Each loop iteration in the brute-force object finder increments this        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         counter; exceeding the maximum causes an IOException to abort.                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. Results After Applying the Patch                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Patch applied cleanly to the four parser classes.                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Fuzzer run still ends with “ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout”.                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - No new exceptions or log messages from the newly added guards were observed,   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         suggesting the code path that hangs may lie outside or before the new checks.       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m. Areas for Further Investigation                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - BruteForceParser’s scanning logic: initial loop conditions and seek/read       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         operations.                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - PDFStreamParser’s token parsing entry point and early exit conditions.         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - XrefParser’s initial xref table discovery [1m([0mbefore the PREV loop[1m)[0m.              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - COSParser’s overall flow in locating the EOF marker and startxref offset.      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Any other loops or recursive calls in the parser chain that lack iteration     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         bounds or early exits.                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Initial Issue Log                                                                [2m                [0m
