[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m84[0m[39m:        try[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m85[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m86[0m[39m:            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m overwrite formerly read bytes[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m87[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytesDecoded > [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m88[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m89[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35mArrays.fill[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdecodedData, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, bytesDecoded, [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m90[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m91[0m[39m:            bytesDecoded = [0m[1;35minflater.inflate[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdecodedData[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m92[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Issue Analysis and Root Cause Identification[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The libFuzzer timeout persists because the parser-level loop guards [0m[1;39m([0m[39min [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCOSParser, XrefParser, PDFStreamParser, BruteForceParser[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m did not cover hangs at [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe filter/decompression layer.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The provided snippet from [0m[1;35mFlateFilterDecoderStream.fetch[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m reveals an [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minfinite-loop scenario when:[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • [0m[1;35minflater.needsInput[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is false [0m[1;39m([0m[39mso no more input is requested[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • [0m[1;35minflater.finished[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is false [0m[1;39m([0m[39mstream not marked complete[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • [0m[1;35minflater.inflate[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdecodedData[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m returns [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m bytesDecoded [0m[1;39m([0m[39mno progress[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In that state, [0m[1;35mfetch[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m returns true [0m[1;39m([0m[39msignaling “I might have data”[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytesDecoded remains [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m. The public [0m[1;35mread[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m method will continually call [0m[1;35mfetch[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithout advancing dataIndex, causing a dead loop and, ultimately, a fuzzer timeout.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Preservation of Existing Logic[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Well-formed compressed streams will either produce data [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytesDecoded > [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msignal [0m[1;35mfinished[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[35m/[0m[95mneedsInput[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. We preserve those flows intact.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In the DataFormatException catch block, we still return any partially read [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdata; that logic remains untouched.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No changes to harness, fuzzing logic, or parser loops beyond this single [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlocation.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Proposed Patch for [0m[1;35mFlateFilterDecoderStream.fetch[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. After calling [0m[1;35minflater.inflate[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdecodedData[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, immediately check for [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mzero-length output:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – If bytesDecoded > [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m: proceed as normal [0m[1;39m([0m[39mreturn true[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – If bytesDecoded == [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m:[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         • If [0m[1;35minflater.finished[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or [0m[1;35minflater.needsInput[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: fall through to [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexisting EOF checks.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         • Otherwise [0m[1;39m([0m[39mno progress possible on a non-finished stream[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, treat as [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mend-of-file:[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             – Set isEOF = true[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             – bytesDecoded = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39malready[0m[1;39m)[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             – Return false to break the read loop.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Replace the unguarded “return true;” at the end of [0m[1;35mfetch[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m with “return [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytesDecoded > [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;” plus the new zero-detection guard.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Implementation Steps[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Open `FlateFilterDecoderStream.java`.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Locate method `private boolean [0m[1;35mfetch[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException`.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Within the `try` block, immediately after[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         bytesDecoded = [0m[1;35minflater.inflate[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdecodedData[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      insert:[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytesDecoded == [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m && ![0m[1;35minflater.finished[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m && ![0m[1;35minflater.needsInput[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m No progress possible: abort to prevent infinite loop[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            isEOF = true;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            return false;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Change the final `return true;` at line [0m[1;36m115[0m[39m to `return bytesDecoded > [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msimply let the existing `return false`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`return true` paths depend on bytesDecoded[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. Rebuild and rerun the fuzzer. The zero-output scenario will now break out of [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe fetch/read loop and surface an IOException or EOF, avoiding a silent hang.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This directly addresses the infinite-loop symptom in the decompression layer, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich was invisible to the earlier parser-level guards.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - It safely breaks corrupt or nonproductive inflate calls without affecting [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalid stream decoding.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No external dependencies, harness, tests, or existing parser logic are [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maltered, ensuring backward compatibility.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Potential Side Effects and Mitigations[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In extremely rare cases of a gradual inflate stream that temporarily returns [0m[1;36m0[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes before later producing output, this patch will prematurely terminate [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdecoding. However, typical zlib behavior either needs input or produces output; a [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtransient [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m-byte inflate without signaling NEEDS_IN[0m[1;33mPUT[0m[39m is itself a flawed zlib [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstate.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Should any legitimate formats be affected, one could implement a small [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mzero-length retry counter [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., allow one or two consecutive zero-length inflate [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalls[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. That refinement can be added if empirical regressions arise.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Run the existing PDFBox test suite to confirm no regressions in valid PDF [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdecoding.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. Next Steps[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Apply this patch to the initial codebase, reapplying prior parser-bound guards[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif not already present.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Execute libFuzzer runs to confirm the timeout no longer occurs.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Optionally, add a regression test with a known problematic compressed stream [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto guard against future regressions.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         ===[33mIssue[0m===                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The project’s libFuzzer harness is consistently timing out when exercising the      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         PDFBox filter decoding logic. The initial issue report shows only the fuzzer        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         timeout message without additional context. A patch was applied to                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `FlateFilterDecoderStream.java` to detect and break out of a potential zero-length  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         inflate loop by marking end-of-file and changing the method’s return condition from [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         an unconditional `true` to `bytesDecoded > [1;36m0[0m`. After applying this patch, the       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         fuzzer still reports a timeout under the same conditions.                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Initial Issue                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The fuzzer invocation ends with [32m"ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout,"[0m indicating that one  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         or more inputs cause the code under test to hang or take too long.                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - No stack trace or exception is shown; the timeout suggests a loop, blocking call, [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         or extensive processing in the inflate/decode path.                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Key observations:                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The timeout arises during filter decoding, specifically in the Flate [1m([0mzlib[1m)[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         inflation routine.                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - There is no immediate crash or exception—execution stalls instead of failing      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         fast.                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The harness merely feeds arbitrary data to `FlateFilterDecoderStream` but is not  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         itself the source of the hang.                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Patch Attempt                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. In `src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/filter/FlateFilterDecoderStream.java`,       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         within the method that inflates compressed data:                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - After calling `[1;35minflater.inflate[0m[1m([0mdecodedData[1m)[0m`, check for `bytesDecoded == [1;36m0[0m`   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         while the inflater is neither finished nor requesting more input.                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - If this “no-progress” state is detected, set `isEOF = true`, force             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `bytesDecoded = [1;36m0[0m`, and return `false` to signal end-of-stream.                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. Change the final `return true;` at the end of the method to `return bytesDecoded [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         > [1;36m0[0m;` so that the decoder signals no further data when zero bytes were produced.    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Patch context [1m([0mline numbers approximate[1m)[0m:                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ```diff                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         @@ [1;36m-89[0m,[1;36m6[0m +[1;36m89[0m,[1;36m14[0m @@                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              bytesDecoded = [1;35minflater.inflate[0m[1m([0mdecodedData[1m)[0m;                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +    [35m/[0m[35m/[0m guard against zero-length inflate causing infinite loops                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +    if [1m([0mbytesDecoded == [1;36m0[0m && ![1;35minflater.finished[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m && ![1;35minflater.needsInput[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m[1m)[0m [1m{[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +        [35m/[0m[35m/[0m No progress possible: abort to prevent infinite loop                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +        isEOF = true;                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +        bytesDecoded = [1;36m0[0m;                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +        return false;                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +    [1m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         @@ [1;36m-112[0m,[1;36m7[0m +[1;36m120[0m,[1;36m7[0m @@                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              [1m}[0m catch [1m([0mDataFormatException exception[1m)[0m [1m{[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                  [35m/[0m[35m/[0m logging                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              [1m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         -    return true;                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +    return bytesDecoded > [1;36m0[0m;                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ```                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Result After Patch                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The fuzzer still terminates with “ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout” under the same test  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         cases.                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - No new errors or exceptions are reported; the hang remains.                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Areas for Further Investigation                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The inflation loop in `FlateFilterDecoderStream` beyond the zero-byte guard:      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         verify state transitions and input buffering logic.                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Interaction between `isEOF`, input-source exhaustion, and how `[1;35mneedsInput[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` is   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         satisfied or starved.                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Overall filter pipeline in `org.apache.pdfbox.filter.*` to see if downstream or   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         upstream loops contribute to stalling.                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - How the harness supplies data and signals end-of-input—ensure that `[1;35msetInput[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         or similar calls occur as intended.                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Exception handling paths: confirm that all `DataFormatException` scenarios break  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         out of loops correctly.                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return false;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This ensures that a stalled inflater is treated as EOF and breaks out of the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minflate loop.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Correct EOF signaling in the bulk-read override [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mread[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m data, int offset, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mint length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Currently, when EOF is encountered on the first fetch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi.e., `[0m[1;35mfetch[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` returns[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfalse immediately[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, `numberOfBytesRead` remains [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m and the method returns [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - According to `InputStream` contract, when no bytes can be read because the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstream is at EOF, the method must return –[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m, not [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Modify the end of the method as follows:[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```diff[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m172[0m[39m:     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m173[0m[39m:     [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m before: return numberOfBytesRead;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m174[0m[39m:     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnumberOfBytesRead == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m175[0m[39m:         [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m no data could be read: signal EOF[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m176[0m[39m:         return [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m177[0m[39m:     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m178[0m[39m:     return numberOfBytesRead;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This change prevents callers [0m[1;39m([0m[39mincluding the fuzzer harness[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m from spinning on [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mzero-length reads, thereby eliminating the hang/timeouts.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Ensure one-byte `[0m[1;35mread[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` semantics remain unchanged:[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The single-byte `[0m[1;35mread[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` already returns –[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m when `isEOF` or `[0m[1;35mfetch[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` signals [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mno more data. Preserve this logic.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Preserve existing DataFormatException handling:[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The logic that logs a warning, computes partial decoded bytes, and returns [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`bytesDecoded > [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m` on exception should remain intact, ensuring partial data is [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreturned before EOF.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Testing and Validation:[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Run existing unit tests for `FlateFilterDecoderStream` to confirm no [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregressions.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Execute the libFuzzer harness to ensure that inputs causing zero-length [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minflation now terminate promptly without timeout.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Test integration scenarios where partial inflate with trailing data triggers [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe DataFormatException path to verify correct EOF behavior.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJustification:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The root cause of the hanging fuzz runs is that bulk `[0m[1;35mread[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` calls return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minstead of –[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m at EOF, causing the harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor upstream filter pipeline[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrepeatedly invoke `read` and never progress or exit.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Aligning `FlateFilterDecoderStream`’s bulk-read with the contract used by [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ASCII85InputStream` ensures proper EOF signaling.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The zero-length inflate guard in `[0m[1;35mfetch[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` prevents infinite inflate loops; [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcombining it with correct EOF return values fully addresses stalling in both [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mone-byte and multi-byte read paths.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All existing filter logic, exception handling, and buffer management remain [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munchanged, preserving functional correctness for valid PDF stream decoding.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No modifications are made to harness code, external libraries, or tests, [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msatisfying project constraints. [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
